description:
In this video, Christian McBride talks about crafting each measure when he plays. McBride practices constantly, even substituting his wife’s arm for a bass when listening to music in the car. 

Read the blog: http://blogs.jwpepper.com/index.php/jazz-100-christian-mcbride-and-the-future-of-jazz?utm_source=youtube&utm_medium=youtube&utm_campaign=jazz100-blogs&utm_content=mcbride-video3

Shop for string bass methods: https://www.jwpepper.com/sheet-music/double-bass-technique-method-books.list?utm_source=youtube&utm_medium=youtube&utm_campaign=jazz100-blogs&utm_content=mcbride-video3

Shop for string bass accessories: https://www.jwpepper.com/sheet-music/2017-string-bass-accessories.list?utm_source=youtube&utm_medium=youtube&utm_campaign=jazz100-blogs&utm_content=mcbride-video3

Filmed on location at Longwood Gardens, Kennett Square, PA https://longwoodgardens.org
Additional studio footage provided by: KNKX Public Radio 88.5 http://knkx.org
Additional studio footage filmed by: Vibe Vision Seattle https://www.facebook.com/vibevisionseattle/
Full-length Sand Dune video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nnFnmcP_ZUQ
Edited by Rocco Richardson
Interviewer: Al Moretti
Featuring: Christian McBride
